giza
------------------------------------------
A 2D scientific plotting library built on cairo. Provides uniform output to
pdf, ps, png and X-Windows. Written in C with no dependencies (other than
cairo) as a direct replacement for PGPLOT.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.0-1
  libX11_6-1.8.10-1
  libcairo2-1.18.4-1
  libfontconfig1-2.16.0-2
  libfreetype6-2.13.3-1
  libgfortran5-12.4.0-3
  libgiza-devel-1.5.0-1bl1
  libgiza2-1.5.0-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.4.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.44-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  flex-2.6.4-2
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-fortran-12.4.0-3
  libX11-devel-1.8.10-1
  libcairo-devel-1.18.4-1
  libfontconfig-devel-2.16.0-2
  libfreetype-devel-2.13.3-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/danieljprice/giza

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/danieljprice/giza/archive/refs/tags/v1.5.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack giza-1.5.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./giza-1.5.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/giza-1.5.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/giza-1.5.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgiza2-1.5.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgiza-devel-1.5.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(giza)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/giza.README
  /usr/share/doc/giza/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/giza/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/giza/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/giza/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/giza/LATEST.md
  /usr/share/doc/giza/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/giza/README.md

(libgiza2)
  /usr/bin/cygcpgplot-2.dll
  /usr/bin/cyggiza-2.dll
  /usr/bin/cygpgplot-2.dll

(libgiza-devel)
  /usr/include/cpgplot.h
  /usr/include/giza-fortran.F90
  /usr/include/giza-shared.h
  /usr/include/giza-version.h
  /usr/include/giza.h
  /usr/lib/gfortran/modules/giza.mod
  /usr/lib/libcpgplot.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libgiza.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libpgplot.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/cpgplot.pc
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/giza.pc
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/pgplot.pc

